## High Humidity

---



[Biome Condition Type](https://origins.readthedocs.io/en/latest/types/biome_condition_types/high_humidity)

Checks whether the biome counts as an area with high humidity (downfall value of > 0.85).

!!! note
    
    If you want functional equality to fire burning out quicker (which was defined via this value in previous Minecraft versions), you should check for the biome tag `minecraft:increased_fire_burnout` with an [In Tag (Biome Condition Type](https://origins.readthedocs.io/en/latest/types/biome_condition_types/high_humidity) instead.

Type ID: `origins:high_humidity`




---

### Examples

```json
"biome_condition": {
    "type": "origins:high_humidity"
}
```
